\ul\b\fs40 1. Description:\ulnone\b0\fs24\par
\tab ECS Swarms is a framework for creating high performance swarm/flocking behaviours built on ECS. Capable of creating fantastic simulations of birds, fish, and so much more!\par
\tab The ECS Swarm Toolkit is \b the asset for you \b0 if you are looking to simply add efficient, swarming/flocking behaviours to your scene. This can be used to create many great effects such as birds, fish, and more! ECS Swarm Toolkit \b is designed to be as simple as possible\b0  as to \b abstract away any complicated ECS code\b0 , it also comes with \b extensive web-based documentation \b0 for you to easily add your own behaviours. It also comes with many built-in behaviours so that you can create your own simulations just by adding a few components, \b no coding required\b0 !\par
\tab It uses ECS and the Physics package, so in order to use you must install the Hybrid Renderer and the Physics packages from the package manager (requires Unity 2022 for Entities 1.0, or Unity 2020 for Entities 0.50). It also supports using the \b Burst compiler \b0 for \b incredible performance!\b0\par
\b Features:\b0\par

